---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="South Portland Dispensary Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to opening a cannabis dispensary in South Portland, Maine. Portland metro market with lower costs."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>South Portland Dispensary Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to open a cannabis dispensary in South Portland, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="Casco Bay Opportunities" type="success">
      South Portland offers the perfect balance of metropolitan access and community feel. By setting up shop here, you're positioning yourself at a strategic gateway to the Casco Bay region. It's a fantastic place to build lasting relationships with both locals and visitors!
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>South Portland, part of the Portland metro area with 25,000+ residents, offers access to the larger Portland market with more affordable real estate costs. Located just across the Casco Bay Bridge, it provides excellent accessibility while avoiding some of Portland's premium costs. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">real estate requirements</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>South Portland Market</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Population</td><td>25,000+ (130k+ metro)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Advantage</td><td>Portland metro access</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Competition</td><td>Moderate</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Real Estate</td><td>Moderate ($15-25/sq ft)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Regulations</td><td>South Portland has local rules</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why South Portland?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Portland Metro</strong> - Access to larger market</li>
        <li><strong>Lower Costs</strong> - More affordable than Portland proper</li>
        <li><strong>Good Traffic</strong> - Major arterials through city</li>
        <li><strong>Growing Area</strong> - New development</li>
        <li><strong>Tourist Adjacent</strong> - Near beaches and attractions</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Locations in South Portland</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Main Street</strong> - Commercial core</li>
        <li><strong>Broadway</strong> - High traffic corridor</li>
        <li><strong>Payless Plaza area</strong> - Shopping district</li>
        <li><strong>Jetport area</strong> - Near airport, high visibility</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment Requirements</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Real Estate (lease)</td><td>$3,000-5,000/mo</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Build-out</td><td>$100,000-200,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Total Investment</td><td>$400,000-800,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Regulations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Check South Portland zoning requirements</li>
        <li>Local license may be required</li>
        <li>Distance requirements from schools</li>
        <li>Signage restrictions apply</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="external-resources">
      <h2>Further Reading & Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.southportland.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">City of South Portland Official Website</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    
    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Stay Ahead of the Curve</h2>
      <p>The cannabis landscape in Maine is constantly evolving. To ensure your business stays compliant and competitive, regularly consult the official resources provided by the <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a>. Their guidelines are the bedrock of a successful, long-term operation.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Cannabis regulations are subject to change; always consult with the Maine Office of Cannabis Policy and qualified legal counsel.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .external-resources { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .further-reading { margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 0.5rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.5rem; }
  .further-reading p { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .external-resources ul { list-style: none; padding-left: 0; }
  .external-resources li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
</style>
